.TH LDM 1 "June 2026" "2.11.0" "Liferay Docker Manager Manual"
.SH NAME
ldm \- Liferay Docker Manager orchestrator (Hardened Edition)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ldm
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR...]
.br
.B ldm
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fINAMESPACE\fR \fISUBCOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBldm\fR is a professional command-line orchestrator for Liferay Portal and DXP environments. It simplifies the creation, management, and synchronization of Liferay instances using Docker Compose, providing near-instant boot times via pre-warmed seeds and seamless integration with Liferay Workspace and Client Extensions.

Commands are organized into logical \fBnamespaces\fR (\fBinfra\fR, \fBcloud\fR, \fBconfig\fR, \fBsystem\fR) for discoverability. All legacy flat-form commands (e.g. \fBldm prune\fR, \fBldm infra-setup\fR) remain fully supported as transparent aliases.

.SH CONFIGURATION REDLINES
.TP
\fBDatabase\fR
All JDBC and Hibernate settings are injected into \fBportal-ext.properties\fR to preserve mixed-case property key integrity (e.g. driverClassName).
.TP
\fBSearch & Infrastructure\fR
Search (ES8), SSL, and Clustering settings are managed via high-priority \fBEnvironment Variables\fR and \fBOSGi .config\fR substitution to ensure project isolation and Sidecar suppression.

.SH OFFLINE FIRST DESIGN
LDM maintains a local cache of all downloaded assets (seeds, samples, configuration templates) in \fB~/.ldm/references\fR. If a project is started without an internet connection, LDM automatically reverts to its cached assets.

.SH CORE COMMANDS
.TP
\fBlist\fR (alias: \fBls\fR)
Display an overview of all initialized LDM sandbox environments.
.TP
\fBrun\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR] (alias: \fBup\fR)
Initialize and start a project stack. Automatically detects context if run inside a project folder. Use \fB--open\fR to launch the browser automatically after startup. Use \fB--scale SERVICE=N\fR to boot a scaled stack in one command.
.TP
\fBstop\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR] [\fISERVICE\fR]
Stop project containers gracefully. Use \fB--all\fR to stop all projects.
.TP
\fBrestart\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR] [\fISERVICE\fR]
Restart containers. Supports \fB--all\fR.
.TP
\fBdown\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR] (alias: \fBrm\fR)
Remove project containers. Use \fB--volumes\fR to also remove data. Use \fB--delete\fR to wipe the project folder.
.TP
\fBstatus\fR (alias: \fBps\fR)
Show status of global infrastructure and projects. Use \fB--all\fR to see stopped projects.
.TP
\fBlogs\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR] [\fISERVICE...\fR]
View real-time logs. Use \fB-f\fR to follow. Use \fB--infra\fR for global service logs. Use \fB--instance N\fR (or \fB-i N\fR) to target a specific replica of a scaled service.
.TP
\fBdeploy\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR]
Hot-deploy built artifacts or rebuild extension images.
.TP
\fBscale\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR] \fISERVICE=N\fR
Scale services within a running project for multi-node or clustering tests.
.TP
\fBbrowser\fR (alias: \fBopen\fR)
Launch the project URL in your system browser.
.TP
\fBwait\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR]
Block execution until Liferay is fully ready (log marker + HTTP 200/302 + CPU idle).
.TP
\fBshell\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR] [\fISERVICE\fR]
Open an interactive bash session in a container.
.TP
\fBgogo\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR]
Connect to the OSGi Gogo shell.
.TP
\fBsnapshot\fR / \fBrestore\fR
Backup and recover exact project states.
.TP
\fBhydrate\fR \fIBACKUP_PATH\fR
Create or restore a project from a local Liferay Cloud backup archive.
.TP
\fBreindex\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR]
Trigger a full Elasticsearch reindex for a project.
.TP
\fBreset\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR]
Clear OSGi state, search data, or database volumes.
.TP
\fBre-seed\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR]
Fully wipe and re-initialize a project from its seed.
.TP
\fBcache\fR (alias: \fBclear-cache\fR, \fBclear-tags\fR)
Clear the local Docker Hub tag cache.
.TP
\fBinfo\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR]
Display formatted project metadata.

.SH DEVELOPMENT COMMANDS
.TP
\fBinit\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR]
Initialize project scaffolding without starting containers.
.TP
\fBinit-from\fR \fISOURCE_PATH\fR [\fINAME\fR]
Initialize a project linked to a source workspace with real-time sync.
.TP
\fBimport\fR \fISOURCE_PATH\fR [\fINAME\fR]
One-time static import of a Liferay workspace.
.TP
\fBmonitor\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR]
Start/restart the background sync process for linked projects.

.SH NAMESPACES
Commands are grouped into namespaces. Legacy flat equivalents are shown in parentheses and remain fully functional.

.SS infra \- Infrastructure Management
.TP
\fBldm infra setup\fR [\fB--search\fR] [\fB--es7\fR]
Start global infrastructure services (Traefik proxy, bridge network). (legacy: \fBldm infra-setup\fR)
.TP
\fBldm infra down\fR
Stop and remove global infrastructure containers. (legacy: \fBldm infra-down\fR)
.TP
\fBldm infra restart\fR [\fB--search\fR]
Reset all global services in one go. (legacy: \fBldm infra-restart\fR)
.TP
\fBldm infra init-common\fR
Recreate the baseline global configuration from internal resources. (legacy: \fBldm init-common\fR)
.TP
\fBldm infra renew-ssl\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR] [\fB--all\fR]
Refresh project-specific SSL certificates. (legacy: \fBldm renew-ssl\fR)
.TP
\fBldm infra migrate-search\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR]
Migrate a project from Sidecar to the shared Global Search container. (legacy: \fBldm migrate-search\fR)

.SS cloud \- Liferay Cloud Integrations
.TP
\fBldm cloud fetch\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR] [\fIENV_ID\fR]
Sync an existing local project directly with a live Liferay Cloud environment. (legacy: \fBldm cloud-fetch\fR)

.SS config \- Configuration Management
All subcommands have backward-compatible flat aliases (e.g. \fBldm env\fR, \fBldm defaults\fR, \fBldm feature\fR, \fBldm log-level\fR, \fBldm edit\fR).
.TP
\fBldm config get\fR [\fIKEY\fR]
Show one or all generic project config values.
.TP
\fBldm config set\fR \fIKEY\fR \fIVALUE\fR
Set a generic project config value.
.TP
\fBldm config remove\fR \fIKEY\fR
Remove a generic project config value.
.TP
\fBldm config defaults\fR [\fIKEY\fR] [\fIVALUE\fR]
View or manage the Cascading Configuration Defaults.
.TP
\fBldm config env\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR]
Manage persistent environment variables in project metadata.
.TP
\fBldm config feature\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR] [\fB--enable\fR|\fB--disable\fR]
Toggle Liferay feature flags.
.TP
\fBldm config log-level\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR]
Manage Liferay internal Log4j2 logging levels without restarts.
.TP
\fBldm config edit\fR [\fIPROJECT\fR]
Open project config files in \fB$EDITOR\fR.

.SS system \- System Utilities & Diagnostics
.TP
\fBldm system doctor\fR
Verify host health, Docker resources, and project dependencies. (legacy: \fBldm doctor\fR)
.TP
\fBldm system prune\fR
Reclaim disk space by removing orphaned containers, search snapshots, and caches. (legacy: \fBldm prune\fR)
.TP
\fBldm system upgrade\fR [\fB--pre-release\fR]
Automatically update \fBldm\fR to the latest stable or pre-release version. (legacy: \fBldm upgrade\fR)
.TP
\fBldm system completion\fR [\fIbash|zsh|fish|powershell\fR]
Configure shell TAB completion. (legacy: \fBldm completion\fR)
.TP
\fBldm system man\fR
Display this manual page. (legacy: \fBldm man\fR)
.TP
\fBldm system fix-hosts\fR [\fIHOSTNAME\fR]
Append missing project hostnames to \fB/etc/hosts\fR. (legacy: \fBldm fix-hosts\fR)
.TP
\fBldm system dev-setup\fR
Configure the LDM development environment. (legacy: \fBldm dev-setup\fR)
.TP
\fBldm system version\fR
Internal version management utility.
.TP
\fBldm system relocate\fR \fITARGET_DIR\fR
Safely move LDM Docker data to an external drive.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable detailed debug logging and granular timing info.
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-non\-interactive\fR
Bypass all prompts and use default values. Ideal for CI/CD.
.TP
\fB\-\-info\fR
Show informational logging (middle tier between standard and debug).
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress informational output.
.TP
\fB\-\-benchmark\fR
Display performance timing after command execution.
.TP
\fB\-\-tag\fR \fITAG\fR
Specify Liferay image tag (e.g. 2025.q1.4-lts).
.TP
\fB\-\-tag\-latest\fR
Automatically discover and use the latest stable Liferay tag.
.TP
\fB\-\-open\fR
(run only) Automatically launch the project URL in your browser after startup.
.TP
\fB\-\-scale\fR \fISERVICE=N\fR [...]
(run only) Boot a scaled stack in one command (e.g. \fB--scale liferay=2\fR).
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-captcha\fR
Disable Omni-Admin CAPTCHA enforcement during initialization.
.TP
\fB\-\-host\-name\fR \fIHOST\fR
Set virtual hostname (defaults to localhost).
.TP
\fB\-\-db\fR \fI{mysql|postgresql|hypersonic}\fR
Select database type.

.SH BACKWARD COMPATIBILITY
All legacy flat commands are automatically translated to their namespaced equivalents by the \fBpreprocess_args\fR layer and remain fully supported indefinitely. For example:
.PP
.nf
ldm prune           \(->  ldm system prune
ldm doctor          \(->  ldm system doctor
ldm infra-setup     \(->  ldm infra setup
ldm cloud-fetch     \(->  ldm cloud fetch
ldm env             \(->  ldm config env
ldm defaults        \(->  ldm config defaults
ldm completion      \(->  ldm system completion
.fi

.SH FILES
.TP
\fB.liferay-docker.meta\fR
Project metadata stored in the project root.
.TP
\fBportal-ext.properties\fR
Liferay configuration in the \fBfiles/\fR subdirectory.
.TP
\fB~/.ldmrc\fR
Global LDM configuration and preferences.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
\fBldm run my-site --samples --open\fR
Quick-start a project with sample extensions and auto-open the browser.
.TP
\fBldm run demo --scale liferay=2\fR
Boot a 2-node Liferay cluster in one command.
.TP
\fBldm logs -f forge\fR
Follow real-time logs for the 'forge' project.
.TP
\fBldm infra setup --search\fR
Start global infrastructure including the shared Elasticsearch container.
.TP
\fBldm system doctor --fix\fR
Run a full health check and apply automatic fixes.
.TP
\fBldm config defaults db_type postgresql\fR
Set PostgreSQL as the default database for all new projects.
.TP
\fBldm cloud fetch my-project uat --restore\fR
Download the latest UAT backup and restore it locally.
.TP
\fBldm system completion zsh\fR
Output the Zsh TAB completion setup command.

